snippet.textDisplay: 2400*1080 for a smartphone is fine. Can we please stop overselling resolution. Yes PenTile matrix displays resolve less than a LCDs but after that “retina” threshold is surpassed a higher resolution isn’t really necessary. That’s just science not some sort of personal preference. Maybe you can have a slightly crisper image with 50ppi more but that’s it and that should be reserved for ridiculously expansive flagships and budged to normal prices phones should prioritize their budged into other more important features.
